<p>Nampa's cold-dry climate requires HVAC systems that excel in both heating efficiency and moderate cooling capacity. Heat pumps are increasingly popular due to their dual functionality and efficiency, though traditional gas furnaces remain viable given Idaho's natural gas availability. For cooling, a SEER rating of 14-16 is typically sufficient for Nampa's moderate summer temperatures, as the dry climate allows evaporative cooling to supplement traditional air conditioning effectively.</p>

