<h2>Nampa Energy Incentives</h2>
<p>Nampa residents have access to several attractive incentives for solar and HVAC upgrades. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% credit on solar installations through 2032, making it an excellent time to invest. For an \$18,000 solar system, this translates to \$5,400 in federal tax credits. Idaho also offers a solar sales tax exemption, saving additional hundreds on installation costs.</p>

<p>Idaho Power provides rebates for qualifying high-efficiency HVAC equipment through their energy efficiency programs. Heat pump rebates can range from \$300 to \$800 depending on the system efficiency, while smart thermostat rebates offer \$50-\$100. Additionally, Idaho Power's Schedule 84 net metering program allows solar customers to receive credit for excess energy produced, though rates are lower than retail electricity prices. The combination of federal, state, and utility incentives can reduce the total cost of solar and HVAC upgrades by 35-40%.</p>

