<p>West Nampa neighborhoods near Lake Lowell benefit from slightly moderated temperatures due to proximity to water, potentially reducing cooling loads. The newer developments around Treasure Valley Marketplace feature larger homes that can accommodate bigger solar arrays, maximizing energy production potential. Rural areas on Nampa's outskirts often have optimal solar exposure with fewer shading concerns but may require additional electrical infrastructure improvements.</p>

<p>Established neighborhoods like Greenhurst and Midland offer a mix of home styles and lot sizes, with many featuring south-facing roofs ideal for solar panel placement. These areas often have mature landscaping that provides natural cooling but requires careful consideration for panel shading throughout the year.</p>

